Given Mkhari definitely doesn t believe in waiting for opportunities or trends on which to capitalise and grow one s business. Rather, he insists on scrutinising and identifying the value that his company can bring to every deal, project or partnership and leveraging it.This probably explains why, amongst a long list of Mkhari s accolades, is the Special Achievement Award presented to him at the Kaelo Awards 2014, for the establishment of the MSG Group and the formation of the POWER 98.7 radio station. The award was given to him in light of his transformative leadership and the significant role he continues to play in the media industry.In this quick insight from a full-length interview, Mkhari reveals his approach to business growth, development and sustainability &#8211; an approach that has resulted in his company, MSG Afrika Investment Holdings, having investments in 15 companies in the media, ICT and communications fields, with operations in over 14 markets on the African continent.Watch the full-length interview here.In partnership with FNB, Moneyweb presents this bespoke leadership video series with top business people. The interview draws on the person s life, failures and the lessons they have learnt on their journey to the successful leadership positions they hold today.Other business leaders share their stories here.